newsitem.title: USA: CBOT overnight Project A ag volume 578 contracts.
newsitem.headline: CBOT overnight Project A ag volume 578 contracts.

text.p: Chicago Board of Trade's Project A overnight agricultural contracts trading volume totaled 578 contracts, according to the CBOT.
There were 52 wheat contracts, 306 corn, 171 soybean, 20 soymeal, and 29 soyoil futures contracts traded, along with 1 corn call and 11 soybean call options.

The overnight trend for corn was 1/4 cent lower to 1-1/4 cents per bushel higher, soybeans one to 4-3/4 cents lower, wheat one to 1-1/2 cents lower, soymeal unchanged to $1 per ton lower, and soyoil 0.02 cent per lb lower.
